                            <comment id="15095811" author="simonstratmann" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 08:24:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you, I was wondering what was up with that, I got it from StackOverflow. Will test as soon as my code compiles again...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15095822" author="tilman" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 08:30:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Which URL - this one?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/a/27986248/535646&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/a/27986248/535646&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15095825" author="simonstratmann" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 08:36:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, the only one that I found explaining how to add links to pages.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15095829" author="tilman" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 08:40:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok - the code you copied from has one difference, the respondent has set a destination for his action, while you didn&apos;t. I suspect PDF.js just saw that an /A entry was there, did nothing (because it was empty) and didn&apos;t bother about the rest.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15095863" author="simonstratmann" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 09:18:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right, I missed that. Thanks for the help.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15096677" author="simonstratmann" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 17:54:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Works fine without the empty action. I&apos;ll close this, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15096696" author="tilman" created="Wed, 13 Jan 2016 18:01:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;set to resolved instead, because there were code changes. Thanks for the feedback.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
